Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, preheat broiler. Season steak with salt and pepper, if desired. Place on unheated rack of broiler pan. Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat 12 to 15 minutes or until desired doneness, turning once. Cook mushrooms in hot oil in medium saucepan about 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in undrained tomatoes, capers and thyme. Bring to boil; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes or until desired consistency. Serve steak and sauce over hot pasta. Garnish with broiled pepper strips, if desired.